&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Manager, Small &amp;amp; Medium Business (SMB)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Location: United States (Remote)&lt;br&gt;Reports To: Director of Sales&lt;br&gt;Employment Type: Full-Time&lt;br&gt;Compensation: $150,000 base salary + 20% target bonus + equity (5,000 options, subject to board approval)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Cargomatic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Cargomatic is transforming the local trucking industry with cutting-edge technology that connects shippers and carriers in real time. Our mission is to bring transparency, efficiency, and reliability to local freight logistics. Backed by leading investors and trusted by some of the world’s largest brands, we are building a smarter, more efficient supply chain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cargomatic, we value ownership, accountability, collaboration, and continuous improvement. If you thrive in a fast-paced, high-growth environment and enjoy building scalable revenue engines, we’d love to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Sales Manager, SMB is responsible for driving revenue growth across a high-velocity segment of small and mid-sized customers. This role will lead, coach, and develop a team of Account Executives while also contributing directly to pipeline development and key deals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on leadership role requiring a balance of strategic thinking and tactical execution. The ideal candidate has a strong background in freight, logistics, or transportation sales and thrives in a performance-driven environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sales Leadership &amp;amp; Team Development&lt;br&gt;· Hire, onboard, and develop a team of SMB Account Executives&lt;br&gt;· Set clear performance expectations and manage team to quota attainment&lt;br&gt;· Coach reps on pipeline generation, deal strategy, and closing techniques&lt;br&gt;· Foster a high-performance, accountable, and collaborative sales culture&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pipeline Development &amp;amp; Revenue Execution&lt;br&gt;· Own team pipeline health, forecasting accuracy, and revenue performance&lt;br&gt;· Drive outbound and inbound sales strategies to generate new business&lt;br&gt;· Partner with marketing to optimize lead flow and conversion rates&lt;br&gt;· Support strategic deals and remove blockers to accelerate close cycles&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Customer &amp;amp; Market Engagement&lt;br&gt;· Build and maintain relationships with shippers, freight brokers, and logistics partners&lt;br&gt;· Develop a deep understanding of customer needs across SMB segments&lt;br&gt;· Stay informed on market trends, pricing dynamics, and competitive landscape&lt;br&gt;· Represent Cargomatic at industry events and customer meetings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;br&gt;· Partner closely with operations to ensure service delivery and customer satisfaction&lt;br&gt;· Align with pricing and finance teams on deal structure and profitability&lt;br&gt;· Collaborate with leadership on go-to-market strategy and sales process improvements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Operational Excellence &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;br&gt;· Track and report on key sales metrics including pipeline, conversion rates, and revenue&lt;br&gt;· Ensure CRM accuracy and disciplined sales processes across the team&lt;br&gt;· Identify opportunities to improve sales efficiency, tooling, and workflows&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;· 5+ years of sales experience in freight, logistics, trucking, or supply chain&lt;br&gt;· 2+ years of experience leading or mentoring sales teams preferred&lt;br&gt;· Proven track record of meeting or exceeding revenue targets&lt;br&gt;· Strong understanding of SMB sales motion and high-velocity s

